<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-07-30T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-07-30T12:00:00-05:00" n="406" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d406">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">856D.10/7–3051: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Indonesia</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-07-30T13:00:00-04:00">July
                                        30, 1951—1 p. m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>120. <gloss target="#t_Eximbank1">Eximbank</gloss> July 26 auth
                                allocation $1,550,000 to assist financing purchase and
                                transportation to Indonesia US equipment materials in connection
                                    <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> Govt forest development
                                program. About $979,000 for four sawmills with necessary rail lines,
                                power plants and work shops and $557,000 for modernization of
                                logging and log transport by truck and trailer.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>